<exercise>
  <p>
    If the different permutations of the word <m>EXAMINATION</m> are listed as in a dictionary, 
    how many items are there in the list before the first word starting with <m>E?</m>
  </p>
  <hint>
    <p>
      List of words in dictionary is arranged in alphabetical order. 
      Hence, the total number of words before starting with <m>E</m> are fixed at <m>A</m> as <m>AAE ----</m>
      <me>
        \frac{10!}{2!2!} =----
      </me>
      where <m>I</m> is repeating twice and <m>N</m> is repeating twice among 10 letters except the first <m>A.</m> 
      Fixed first <m>A</m> and then remaining letters <m>A E I I M N O N T X.</m>
    </p>
  </hint>
</exercise>

<exercise>
 <statement>
  <p>
    Find the number of word which can be made using all the letters of the word <m>AGAIN.</m>
        <me>
        \frac{5!}{2!} = 60.
      </me>
    </p>
    <p>
    If these words are written as in a dictionary what will be the <m>50^{th}</m> word?
  </p>
 </statement>
  <solution>
       <p>
      <ol marker ="i.">
        <li>
          <p>
            In alphabetical order <m>A A G I N </m>
           </p>
          <p>
            For the word starts with <m>A</m> fix its position at first place and then <m>A G I N</m>
            <me>
              4! =24.
            </me>
            No repetition in <m>A G I N</m>.
          </p>
          </li>
          <li>
             <p>
                For the word starts with <m>G</m> fix its position at first place and then <m>A A I N</m>
                <me>
                  \frac{4!}{2!} =12
                </me>
                </p>
           </li>
           <li>
            <p>
              For the word starts with <m>I</m> fix its position at first place and then <m>A A G N</m>
              <me>
                \frac{4!}{2!} =12
              </me>
              </p>
              <p>
                Total words count = <m>24+12+12= 48.</m>
              </p>
           </li>
           <li>
            <p>
              for the word at <m>49^{th}</m> position in a list, fix <m>N</m> and then <m>AAGI</m> 
            </p>
           </li>
           <li>
            <p>
              for the word at <m>50^{th}</m> position in a list, fix <m>N</m> and then <m>AAIG</m> 
            </p>
           </li>
      </ol>
    </p>
  </solution>
</exercise>


